&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ASSOCIATE SOFTWARE ENGINEER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mesh Optical Technologies was founded on the belief that optical photons will be at the center of advanced technologies in the coming century. Making advanced technology ubiquitous means building at scale, and that&#39;s exactly what we&#39;re doing at Mesh.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our interns and co-ops are embedded in the engineering team and own real work—not side projects. We are seeking an Associate Software Engineer to contribute directly to the codebase that operates both our optical interconnect product and factory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with your mentor to implement and test bare-metal drivers for I²C, SPI, ADC, DMA, and other interfaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in node bring-up from power-on to firmware load, capturing boot logs and helping debug hardware-software interactions in the lab&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gain experience designing and implementing algorithms for link optimization and per-unit calibration in C++ and Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Come up with new software-enabled ways to automatically validate device operation and production processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BASIC QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pursuing or recently completed a BS or MS in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or a related field with a GPA of 3.5 or greater&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Portfolio of hands-on projects with a hardware element: embedded firmware, robotics, signal-processing, etc. for Formula SAE, SolarCar, Robotics, CubeSats, or other club/personal builds. Portfolios of software-only projects will not be considered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to I²C, SPI, ADC sampling, or similar protocols, and a curiosity for low-level hardware interfaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Python and C or C++ and comfort working in a Linux environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical mindset, first-principles problem solving, and clear communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREFERRED SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your projects demonstrate not just software engineering aptitude but also multidisciplinary knowledge of electrical engineering and mechanical engineering concepts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMPENSATION AND BENEFITS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pay range:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Associate Software Engineer: $26.00 - $38.00/per hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Base salary is determined based your academic year. In addition to base salary, compensation for this role includes a flexible monthly housing and transportation stipend during your time in Los Angeles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ELECTRICAL ENGINEER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mesh Optical Technologies was founded on the belief that optical photons will be at the center of advanced technologies in the coming century. Making advanced technology ubiquitous means building at scale, and that’s exactly what we’re doing at Mesh.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our products integrate precision optics and advanced packaging. The electrical systems that drive, control, and test them must meet the same performance and manufacturability bar. We are seeking an Electrical Engineer to design, validate, and debug high-speed PCB assemblies across our optical hardware platform. You will work closely with senior engineers to support board bring-up, signal integrity validation, and development of the test infrastructure required for production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and support multilayer PCB assemblies for high-speed optical hardware, including power delivery, signal routing, and connector/interface selection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with schematic capture and PCB layout under senior engineering guidance, applying controlled impedance routing and signal integrity best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support board bring-up, electrical validation, and lab debugging for prototype and production hardware&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform signal integrity validation using lab instrumentation (oscilloscopes, VNAs, TDR, logic analyzers) and correlate measurements to design intent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support development of evaluation platforms for new silicon, interconnect, and photonic components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to end-of-line test infrastructure, including test fixture design, firmware flashing workflows, and automated validation sequences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally with firmware, mechanical, optical, and manufacturing engineering teams to ensure electrical designs support system integration and production scalability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support electrical documentation, including schematics, BOMs, assembly drawings, and test procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s or Master&#39;s degree in electrical engineering or a related discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience designing or validating hardware systems (internships or substantive project experience considered)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with schematic capture and PCB layout tools (Altium or equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foundational understanding of signal integrity, controlled impedance routing, and high-speed PCB design principles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with lab instrumentation (oscilloscopes, logic analyzers, power supplies, spectrum analyzers)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong debugging and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to work extended hours and weekends as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREFERRED EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with high-speed digital interfaces (e.g., SerDes, PCIe, Ethernet, LVDS, or MIPI)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with firmware flashing and debug workflows (JTAG, SWD, ISP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to automated test or manufacturing environments, including test fixture development or production test integration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scripting or data analysis experience (e.g., Python, MATLAB) for test automation or measurement post-processing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with power integrity analysis, PDN design, or power supply selection and validation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with EMC/EMI design practices and regulatory compliance considerations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with rigid-flex or high-density interconnect (HDI) PCB design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with configuration management and revision control for electrical de

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ELECTRICAL INTEGRATION &amp;amp; TEST ENGINEER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mesh Optical Technologies was founded on the belief that optical photons will be at the center of advanced technologies in the coming century. Making advanced technology ubiquitous means building at scale, and that’s exactly what we’re doing at Mesh.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an Electrical Integration &amp;amp; Test Engineer to own the electrical integration of production equipment, test systems, and development lab infrastructure. You will get deeply familiar with the electrical design of our products and production systems and are expected to participate in every step of the integration process—from line bring-up and debug through production ramp and sustained operation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the electrical integration of production equipment, test systems, and workstations across manufacturing lines and development labs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead electrical bring-up, debug, and validation of new and modified production cells and test stations, resolving issues across power, signal, controls, and instrumentation boundaries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-of-line test systems and development lab test assets, including their electrical hardware, cabling, instrumentation interfaces, and long-term operational reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, integrate, and maintain electrical test fixtures, cable assemblies, and hardware interfaces used for qualification, validation, and manufacturing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and maintain electrical interfaces between tools, instruments, fixtures, and factory infrastructure, including power distribution, grounding, and signal routing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as front-line electrical engineering support for the production floor, troubleshooting electrical issues and driving rapid resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate proposed designs for electrical integration feasibility, providing feedback on connector access, cable routing, test point placement, and debug accessibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate nonconformances and electrical failures to determine root cause and drive corrective action and system improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive test readiness for new product introductions, revisions, and production ramps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface with both engineers and technicians to optimize electrical integration, test, and automation workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in electrical engineering, computer engineering, or a related engineering discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years of hands-on experience in electrical integration, test, hardware debug, or manufacturing (internships, co-ops, and substantive project experience qualify)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with electrical schematics, wiring diagrams, and system-level electrical documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with lab instrumentation (oscilloscopes, multimeters, logic analyzers, power supplies)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong electrical debugging and troubleshooting skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated engineering intuition, critical thinking, and comfort with ambiguity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to work extended hours and weekends as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREFERRED EXPERIENCE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with optical, RF, or high-speed electrical test equipment (e.g., VNAs, BERTs, optical power meters, high-bandwidth oscilloscopes)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience integrating or maintaining multi-station production test systems or factory automation equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing electrical test fixtures, probe interfaces, or cable assemblies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with data acquisition systems, instrument co

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EMBEDDED CONTROLS ENGINEER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mesh Optical Technologies was founded on the belief that optical photons will be at the center of advanced technologies in the coming century. Making advanced technology ubiquitous means building at scale, and that’s exactly what we’re doing at Mesh.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our products and factory equipment rely on real-time control systems that must be precise, stable, and fast—from thermal regulation and optical alignment loops to motion control and process automation. We are seeking an Embedded Controls Engineer who combines deep embedded programming expertise with strong controls and algorithms knowledge. You will design, implement, and tune the control systems that keep our hardware operating at the edge of its performance envelope.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and tune real-time control loops (PID, state-space, feedforward, adaptive) for thermal management, optical alignment, motion control, and process regulation across product and factory systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop embedded firmware in C/C++ for microcontrollers and DSPs, including bare-metal and RTOS-based architectures, with emphasis on deterministic timing and low-latency execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Model and simulate control systems to predict dynamic behavior, assess stability margins, and validate controller designs prior to hardware deployment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement sensor fusion, filtering (Kalman, complementary), and signal conditioning algorithms to extract clean, actionable signals from noisy real-world measurements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring up and integrate new sensors, actuators, and motor drives, defining hardware-software interfaces and writing low-level drivers (I²C, SPI, ADC, PWM, encoder interfaces)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop calibration routines and self-tuning algorithms that enable production-scale deployment of control systems with unit-to-unit variation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Instrument control systems for observability—logging, telemetry, and diagnostic interfaces that support real-time monitoring, fault detection, and post-hoc analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with electrical, mechanical, optical, and manufacturing engineering teams to co-design systems where control performance is tightly coupled to hardware design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support production deployment of control systems, including validation, fault handling, and graceful degradation strategies for field-deployed units&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to Python-based tooling for system identification, data analysis, simulation, and automated testing of control system performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s or Master&#39;s degree in electrical engineering, computer engineering, mechanical engineering, aerospace engineering, or a related discipline with coursework in control systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience designing and implementing real-time control systems on embedded platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency in C and/or C++ for embedded development, including experience with bare-metal and RTOS environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid foundation in classical and modern control theory, including PID tuning, frequency-domain analysis, and stability assessment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with sensor integration, actuator interfacing, and low-level peripheral drivers (I²C, SPI, ADC, PWM, encoders)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Python or MATLAB for modeling, simulation, data analysis, and test automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong debugging skills across hardware and software boundaries, including use of oscilloscopes, logic analyzers, and serial debug interfaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently in fast-moving, cross-functional environments&lt;/l

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FACILITIES DIRECTOR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mesh Optical Technologies was founded on the belief that optical photons will be at the center of advanced technologies in the coming century. Making advanced technology ubiquitous means building at scale, and that’s exactly what we’re doing at Mesh.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we embark on this journey to operate the highest-volume optical manufacturing facility in North America, we are seeking a Facilities Director to develop efficient, safe, clean, and high-capacity production environments to support an aggressive production ramp.&amp;nbsp;As Facilities Director, you will lead the strategic design, rapid implementation, and ongoing management of our facility infrastructure to support high-volume optical manufacturing. You will oversee the specification, procurement, and commissioning of critical systems—power, electrical, network, exhaust, air, and HVAC—ensuring they are built to meet the demands of our cutting-edge production line while maintaining safety, compliance, and operational excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design and build-out of facility infrastructure, including power distribution, electrical systems, network infrastructure, exhaust systems, cleanroom air quality, and HVAC, to support high-volume optical manufacturing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage construction activities, vendor partnerships, and overall project execution to ensure rapid deployment aligned with aggressive production ramp schedules and long-term operational objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all facility systems and operations comply with applicable EHS/OSHA standards, fire safety codes, building regulations, insurance requirements, and environmental laws.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize facility layout and space utilization — including equipment placement, workstations, and access control — to support efficient, large-scale manufacturing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement data-driven facilities management systems to enhance efficiency, reduce operational costs, and promote sustainability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commission, operate, and maintain critical infrastructure systems, establishing preventative maintenance schedules and monitoring tools to ensure high uptime and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with engineering and production teams to align facility capabilities with manufacturing equipment needs, such as die-bonding, flip-chip assembly, and automated optical inspection systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead root-cause investigations for facility or system downtime, driving corrective actions to minimize disruptions and optimize performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute long-term facility expansion strategies, including identification, evaluation, and planning of new leases or acquisitions to support company growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Construction Management, Mechanical Engineering, a related field, or extensive prior experience with exceptional performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of overseeing facility build-outs and infrastructure upgrades for high-volume production environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong project management and leadership skills, with experience managing cross-functional teams, vendors, and contractors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills, with experience collaborating across engineering, manufacturing, and executive functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on problem-solving skills, with the ability to troubleshoot and resolve issues in electrical, mechanical, or HVAC systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to work extended hours and weekends as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
